descript.abstract: Shapefile of the geographic boundary of Denver Water's treated water Service Area. There are no restrictions on what Denver Water can do within the service area; the service area includes the connectors and other facilities where we provide water. It provides the flexibility to serve general areas when new services are needed (ex: SA for State Parks includes present locations of bathrooms, which might move in the future, so DW service area includes the entire park) and It includes all of our “connectors” (points or entities we serve that aren’t actually in a district (ex: fed center, some of our properties), bulk ZIP code areas, Chatfield and Cherry Creek State Parks.The Denver Water Service Area boundary should be use for maps that aren’t specifically geared toward Distributor boundaries. The name in the legend should be DW Service Area.
descript.purpose: To reference the geographic boundary of Denver Water's treated water Service.
